paragraph.text:
the term
				flexible fuel vehicle means a vehicle that has been warranted by
				its manufacturer to operate on gasoline, E85, and M85;

the term E85 means a fuel
				mixture containing up to 85 percent ethanol and meets the standards of ASTM
				D5798;

the term M85 means a fuel
				mixture containing up to 85 percent methanol and meets the standards of ASTM
				D5797;

the term biodiesel means
				diesel fuel which has been produced from a non-petroleum feedstock and which
				meets the standards of ASTM D6751–03;

